:\n  branches/changes/PRs actually changed or operated on\n```\n\nThen PR trail should use `active targets` for strong inclusion, and only use ambient targets as weak fallback when there’s no better evidence.\n\nSo: the patch I made fixes the “old applied PR branch polluted a read-only/new investigation session” case, but it does **not** fully solve multi-applied-branch attribution.","tool_name":null,"tool_input":null,"source_record":{"timestamp":"2026-05-26T13:12:52.739Z","type":"response_item","payload":{"type":"message","role":"assistant","phase":"final_answer"}}}